<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-10T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="645" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">600.119/1803a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-10T22:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1918—10 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>3367. For Sheldon [from War Trade Board]: No. 1822. Please advise us what if
                        any proposals have been formulated by the A.B.C. for shipments to Servia,
                        Bulgaria Turkey including Syria.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>